&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;2022/2023 Academic Year Sabbatical Report:&lt;br&gt;Workforce Development Study:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;During my sabbatical in the 2022/2023 academic year, I worked to enhance my expertise in employee development within the construction industry. The primary goal was to explore innovative methods for fostering the professional growth of construction workers, supervisors, and managers. Additionally, I worked with Procore Construction Management Software to develop educational content for use in higher education, and I worked with the United Brotherhood of Carpenters (UBC) to develop educational content for use in training supervisory personnel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Objectives:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;span style=&quot;font:7pt 'Times New Roman';&quot;&gt;      &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Investigate Current Practices: Gain a comprehensive understanding of the existing employee development practices in the construction industry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;span style=&quot;font:7pt 'Times New Roman';&quot;&gt;      &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Identify Gaps and Challenges: Analyze the shortcomings and obstacles hindering effective employee development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;span style=&quot;font:7pt 'Times New Roman';&quot;&gt;      &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Develop Customized Training Programs: Create training modules to address the specific needs of construction professionals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;span style=&quot;font:7pt 'Times New Roman';&quot;&gt;      &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Explore Technological Solutions: Investigate the role of technology, and enhance employee development in the use of those technologies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Study Methodologies:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;span style=&quot;font:7pt 'Times New Roman';&quot;&gt;      &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Assessment of Job Description, and Roles and Responsibilities: I reviewed documents detailing the job descriptions, and roles and responsibilities of varying positions within the construction industry, (Project Executive, Senior Project Manager, Project Manager, Project Engineer, and Project Coordinator), as well as the job descriptions, and roles and responsibilities of&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;field supervision personnel (Senior Superintendent, Superintendent, Assistant Superintendent). I further reviewed documents detailing specific procedures to be followed when managing and supervising a project.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;span style=&quot;font:7pt 'Times New Roman';&quot;&gt;      &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Assessment of Software Applications: I reviewed construction specific software being used in the construction industry to gain an understanding of the operation, benefits, limitations, and difficulties in using the applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;span style=&quot;font:7pt 'Times New Roman';&quot;&gt;      &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Employee Interviews: I conducted interviews with construction professionals at various levels to gain insights into their on-board training, continuing training, training needs, preferences, and areas of difficulty.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;span style=&quot;font:7pt 'Times New Roman';&quot;&gt;      &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Identifying Skill Gaps: Through analysis of collected data, I identified skill gaps and areas for improvement. These included technical skills, and soft skills, such as leadership, communication, and problem-solving.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;span style=&quot;font:7pt 'Times New Roman';&quot;&gt;      &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Training Module Design: The findings formed the basis for tailoring comprehensive training modules for use by individual construction companies, as well as by software companies, and training organizations. &lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;span style=&quot;font:7pt 'Times New Roman';&quot;&gt;      &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Feedback and Iteration Design: Following the development of training modules, I developed methodologies to collect feedback from participants, with the goal of making improvements to the modules.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;span style=&quot;font:7pt 'Times New Roman';&quot;&gt;      &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Technology Integration: I explored the potential of technology in employee development. This integration included researching the use of mobile technologies, software, and e-learning platforms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Workforce Development&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Company #1 – Workforce Development&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At company #1, I assessed the current operational processes being used to discover challenges being confronted, and processes that have opportunities for improvement. To accomplish this task, I worked with corporate management, project management, contract administrators, construction personnel, and others directly involved in the operations of the company. I reviewed current processes, and conducted interviews with individuals within the operational processes to gain an understanding of current operations and document the opinions and suggestions of those personnel.&lt;span&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Company #1 Outcomes and Deliverables:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;span style=&quot;font:7pt 'Times New Roman';&quot;&gt;      &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Provided corporate management an assessment of current operations management processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;span style=&quot;font:7pt 'Times New Roman';&quot;&gt;      &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Provided proposed modifications, deletions, and additions to the current operation processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;span style=&quot;font:7pt 'Times New Roman';&quot;&gt;      &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Provided an assessment of the benefits and detriments of the proposed changes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;span style=&quot;font:7pt 'Times New Roman';&quot;&gt;      &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Provided an implementation plan detailing processes for implementing proposed changes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;span style=&quot;font:7pt 'Times New Roman';&quot;&gt;      &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Proposed processes and content for operations management development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Company #2 -&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;Workforce Development:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;At company #2, I identified and provided an assessment of project management personnel best practices and work processes required to be performed at each level of management. Once identified, upstream and downstream stakeholders, including corporate management, office personnel, and field supervisory personnel were interviewed to establish best practices employed by current project management personnel. Working with company personnel, levels of management were established and metrics were determined to provide criteria for each level. Assessment measures were developed for upstream management to assess the progress of achievement of progressing project management personnel.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Company #2 Outcomes and Deliverables:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;span style=&quot;font:7pt 'Times New Roman';&quot;&gt;      &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Provided to corporate management an assessment of the current best practices of project management personnel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;span style=&quot;font:7pt 'Times New Roman';&quot;&gt;      &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Provided proposed modifications, deletions, and additions to the current development processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;span style=&quot;font:7pt 'Times New Roman';&quot;&gt;      &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Provided metrics for achieving varying levels of project management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;span style=&quot;font:7pt 'Times New Roman';&quot;&gt;      &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Provided tools for assessing progress of personnel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;span style=&quot;font:7pt 'Times New Roman';&quot;&gt;      &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Provided corporate management an assessment of current operations management processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;·&lt;span style=&quot;font:7pt 'Times New Roman';&quot;&gt;      &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Proposed &lt;span&gt;the development of training modules to foster employee growth, as well as proposed to deliver on-site and remote training, tailored for personnel in specific hard and soft skills.&lt;span&gt;    &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Procore Learning Module:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In line with my commitment to workforce development, I worked with Procore construction management software in creating learning modules. The scenario-based learning modules allow users to simulate real construction scenarios within the Procore environment. The educational content was developed to facilitate the adoption and use of Procore within higher education construction management and engineering curricula.&lt;/p&gt;
